<section class="page-hero"><div class="container"><div class="eyebrow">About The Scuba Buddha</div><h1>Diving with purpose.</h1><p>Built around patience, discipline, inclusion, and the belief that strong divers are developed through understanding—not shortcuts.</p></div></section>
<section class="section alt"><div class="container grid-2"><div class="image-panel"></div><div><h2>Neal Hamilton</h2><p class="lead">Owner • SDI Instructor • TDI Instructor</p>
<p>After 21 years of service in the U.S. Army, Neal brought the same commitment to preparation, calm decision-making, accountability, and team development into scuba instruction.</p>
<p>He began diving in 2015. The experience became more than recreation—it became a source of peace, personal growth, challenge, and community. The Scuba Buddha exists to help divers build that same meaningful relationship with the underwater world.</p>
<div class="notice"><strong>Instruction philosophy:</strong> Slow down, understand the “why,” master the fundamentals, and build confidence that lasts beyond the certification card.</div></div></div></section>
<section class="section sand"><div class="container"><h2>What guides every course</h2><div class="grid-3">
